
.content-parent
  .title-area
    %h1 This is the page title.
    %h1 It's a html "h1" tag.
    %h1 H1 always uses the corporate Font, Netto.

.content-parent
  .content-area-1.positiveContent
    %h2 This is content that provides a user some useful or positive information.
    %p It can be used anywhere on the page, and will often have content in it that's dependent on what information the user has told us, such as their maximum capacity and export, or what ratings their property already has.

  .content-area-1.instructionContent
    %h2 This is content that provides the user a prompt to do something, like change their inverters
    %p It can be used anywhere on the page, and just like the green box, will often have content in it that's dependent on what information the user has told us.

  .content-area-1
    %h2 This is the header for the first content area, it's an "h2" tag.
    %h2 Everything that's an H2 and below should use Arial or Sans Serif.
    %p This some body text, it uses the html "p" tag. Body text should use Arial or Sans Serif font-families.
    %p Body should use sentence case.



  .content-area-1
    %h1
      %b Page Elements
    %h1 This is a Page Header, h1
    %h2 This is a Section Header, h2
    %h3 This is a Sub-section Header, h3
    %h4 This is a Sub-section Header, h4
    %br
    %h2
      %b Binary Questions
    %p Many of the options in the Pre-Approval Prototype are "yes / no" or similar questions, with additional questions depending on this answer.
    = render "layouts/yes-or-no"
    %br
    %h2
      %b Forms
    %h3 Input fields:
    .text-input
      %form
        %label This is a multiple choice dropdown
        %select{:class=>"multipleChoice"}
          %option{:value=>"1"} Option 1
          %option{:value=>"2"} Option 2
          %option{:value=>"3"} Option 3
        %label This is a free text field
        %input
        %label This is a free text field with a warning - use it if validation fails, or a user has forgotten to add the right information.
        %input.warning
    %br
    %h3
      %b Radio Buttons
    %p use these if you want a user to select only one of a few different options
    %form
      .checkbox
        %input{:type=>"radio", :id=>"styleguideRadio1", :name=>"styleguideRadio", :class=>"styleguideRadio"}
        %label{:for=>"Option1"} This is a radio option
      .checkbox
